author: duftler
msg: Committed 1st pass at tool to convert from WSDL1.1 to WSDL2.0.
Added the necessary lines to build.xml and build.properties to allow building (requires WSDL4J).
Made a minor change to build.xml to stop Xerces jars from being repeatedly extracted.
Try "java org.apache.woden.tool.converter.Convert" to see command-line usage.
Currently outputs files with the same name as inputted, but with an ".wsdl2" extension.
Can be modified to output Woden classes.
